The Borno State Police Command has arrested a notorious fraudster, a Cameroonian, Musa Isa  at Muna Garage IDPs camp for defrauding IDPs by giving to them fake NGO food cards tagged , “JERE TCHAD SABILLILAHI” , and collecting N200 from each person under the guise that the foodstuff will be supplied to them. Narrating to newsmen the modus operandi of the Cameroonian fraudster, yesterday in Maiduguri, the Commander SARS of the police, Mr Mohammed Ibrahim, said the culprit disguises as somebody from an NGO or humanitarian agency to dupe his victims. According to the SARS Commander, the suspect usually entered into the IDPs camps in connivance with his Nigerian staffers. Ibrahim said:” Very early in the morning, you will see about 3,000 to 4,000 IDPs queuing up to pay for these fake food cards. “ He is a Cameroonian by indigene, but disguise as Chadian while operating.  It was until we liaised with the Chadian embassy which made all the enquiries before it was discovered that he is not a Chadian, but a Cameroonian through his passport. “ He has a Cameroonian passport and had nothing to do with Chad. So those managing the IDPs camps should be mindful of the people they let into the camps. “ Another similar case was where females IDPs were made to pay as much as N5,000 for fake food cards from another fake NGO. The victims who are mostly women usually rush to collect for their family members, with some collecting for about 30 of the food cards only to later discover that they were fake,” the SARS Commander further said. Also arrested for impersonation and attempt to commit felony is one Abdullahi Al- Amin who impersonated a DSS personnel with intent to defraud one Bulama Grema of Moronti ward Maiduguri and one Fatima Bosuma of the sum of N150,000 respectively. The police said that Al- Amin would be charged to court at the conclusion of investigation.